s=\"(max-width: 2048px) 100vw, 2048px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>STARTS:<\/strong> 20th September, 15:00 UTC<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>ENDS:<\/strong> 23rd September, 09:00 UTC<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Heracles wandered through the blackened hallways for what seemed like centuries. Staircases changed direction, and doors recoiled as he reached out his hand to touch them. In the darkness he continued onwards, the runes of Excalibur his only light.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Turning a corner it came into view, a cosmic hourglass upon an altar glowing gently in the pitch black chamber. Heracles did not direct himself to touch it, but his arms moved nonetheless, and his fingers stretched around the relic.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>In that moment, the <\/em><strong><em>Singularity<\/em><\/strong><em> racked Heracles&#8217; mind as he fell to the ground, and visions of time flashed before his eyes. Frozen in place, every moment played for him; the clash of Korthan and Almarand\u2019s swords, putting into motion a symphony of violence and war. The Gods of Olympus, Asgard, and the Egyptian realms all weaving their own melodies into the song of the Shattered Kingdoms. The visions crescendoed as Heracles watched the fall of the Archmage tower, and the arrival of the primordial powers, with a final vision focusing on his own passage through the portal into the Nexus realm.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Returning back to the darkened chamber, Heracles sensed he was not alone. Whipping around, Excalibur in hand, the darkness of the room betrayed nothing but the glowing of two corrupted eyes. The shape shifted in the room, spinning Heracles on an axis, with a subtle laughter that filled his ears.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u2018Welcome, son of Olympus. You have performed your part exceptionally.\u2019 A voice whispered. Heracles looked back to the hourglass, when time slowed to a crawl and the final drop passed from the top bulb to the bottom.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>With that, the figure emerged. Heracles recognised him from the vision, but he did not have time to think. <\/em><strong><em>Almarand<\/em><\/strong><em> lunged with a downward strike of his corrupted sword, to which Heracles raised Excalibur. The swords of the cataclysm joined each other once again, and the chamber flashed in white light.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Heracles awoke on a plinth in the Shattered Kingdoms. Opening his eyes to the sky he realised what he had done. The veil of the realms had been sundered, and the servants of darkness poured into the world as the prophecy foretold.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/single2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1762\" width=\"518\" height=\"512\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/single2.png 691w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/single2-300x297.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 518px) 100vw, 518px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>This relic promises to be a mighty strategic asset for players hoping to claim mastery of the Nexus.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>More details around the <strong>Armageddon <\/strong>event (Thursday 23rd of September) will be shared in a blog post early next week.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Milestone Rewards<\/strong> are as follows:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"412\" height=\"890\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/single_track.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1758\" s